coronet is a derivative work of co_context, with the following major changes:

- Cross-platform support: added Windows IOCP backend (co_context is Linux-only)
- Static polymorphism: replaced virtual base proactor class with C++20 concepts
  and compile-time platform selection
- Modern C++ refactoring: std::unique_ptr ownership, constexpr where possible,
  reduced macro usage in favor of metaprogramming
- Extended API: when_all/when_any/when_some combinators, defer utility,
  timeout_at, async::read/write (Windows background thread)
- I/O operation recycling: per-thread free list (ASIO pattern) for IOCP path
- Build system: CMake cross-platform build with external dependency management
- Comprehensive test suite: 11 test programs covering all core APIs
- Performance benchmarks: redis-echo comparison across GCC/Clang/MSVC

Original co_context source files that were substantially modified are located
under include/coronet/ and lib/coronet/. The architecture design, io_uring
integration patterns, and basic coroutine infrastructure (task, generator,
shared_task, SPSC ring) trace their lineage to co_context.

For the original work, see: https://github.com/Codesire-Deng/co_context
